ture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/013/642/e4fdbdb735ac2b938c6eb072303166bc708a9a50_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"basecamp","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":9231557,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hi @jouko,\n\nThanks again for the report.\n\nWe rewrite CSS in `\u003cstyle\u003e` tags for a variety of reasons—for example, to proxy third-party images in `url('...')` values. The HTML parsing library we use supports updating the content of an element with HTML or text. Unfortunately, we were inserting filtered CSS as HTML rather than text.\n\nWe just shipped a change that we believe closes this vulnerability. Would you mind confirming?","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2020-09-15T21:48:59.858Z","updated_at":"2020-09-15T21:48:59.858Z","actor":{"username":"georgeclaghorn","cleared":false,"url":"/georgeclaghorn","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/019/774/ca6398181b4bb7b5b1b34ac9c1fb592a799e9239_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"basecamp","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":9231569,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::ReportSeverityUpdated","message":"","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2020-09-15T21:53:11.937Z","updated_at":"2020-09-15T21:53:11.937Z","additional_data":{"old_severity":"High","new_severity":"Critical","old_severity_id":846846,"new_severity_id":847044},"actor":{"username":"georgeclaghorn","cleared":false,"url":"/georgeclaghorn","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/019/774/ca6398181b4bb7b5b1b34ac9c1fb592a799e9239_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"basecamp","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":9231588,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BountyAwarded","message":"We discussed this vulnerability internally and decided to bump it up to the critical tier because it could have been exploited to take over staff accounts and access sensitive admin tools. Accordingly, we’re awarding an additional $3,500 to bring the total for this report to $5,000.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2020-09-15T21:57:08.493Z","updated_at":"2020-09-15T21:57:08.493Z","actor":{"url":"/basecamp","ibb":false,"profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/STtZ2opgRsHdKby72xs56KhB/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"profile":{"name":"Basecamp"}},"bounty_amount":"3500.0","bounty_currency":"usd","bonus_amount":"0.0","genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"basecamp","collaborator":{"username":"jouko","url":"/jouko"},"actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":9232195,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Nice! Yes, that patch seems to have fixed it.\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2020-09-16T02:15:41.387Z","updated_at":"2020-09-16T02:15:41.387Z","actor":{"username":"jouko","cleared":false,"url":"/jouko","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/013/642/e4fdbdb735ac2b938c6eb072303166bc708a9a50_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"basecamp","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":9232256,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugResolved","message":"Great, thank you!","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2020-09-16T02:41:53.124Z","updated_at":"2020-09-16T02:41:53.124Z","actor":{"username":"georgeclaghorn","cleared":false,"url":"/georgeclaghorn","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/019/774/ca6398181b4bb7b5b1b34ac9c1fb592a799e9239_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"reporter":{"username":"jouko","url":"/jouko"},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"basecamp","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":9232408,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"It's sort of my first positive bug bounty experience this year (haven't been very active). And the first time I get bounty on triage (instead of months of waiting). And probably the first time the sum was increased after internal investigation. I thought I could tweet about it - it's nice for a change to have something positive to tell about bug bounties. It would be also nice to give some kind of shoutout to teams who do it right. Would that be OK? I can of course just tweet without mentioning the program or asset if it's against your policy.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2020-09-16T03:14:09.061Z","updated_at":"2020-09-16T03:14:09.061Z","actor":{"username":"jouko","cleared":false,"url":"/jouko","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/013/642/e4fdbdb735ac2b938c6eb072303166bc708a9a50_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"basecamp","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":9236497,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"We’re glad you had a positive experience!\n\nYou're welcome to tweet, and you can mention HEY. Our HackerOne program is private, though—we’re still working our way up to a manageable public program—so we’d prefer if you didn’t mention it. If people ask, you can direct them to our [security response page](https://hey.com/policies/security/response/).","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2020-09-16T12:55:20.441Z","updated_at":"2020-09-16T12:55:20.441Z","actor":{"username":"georgeclaghorn","cleared":false,"url":"/georgeclaghorn","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/019/774/ca6398181b4bb7b5b1b34ac9c1fb592a799e9239_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"basecamp","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":9238180,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"If I tweet about a bug bounty related to HEY, won't it be obvious you run a bounty program?\n\nJust to be sure, which part are you OK with to reveal?\n\n1) I got a bug bounty\n2) related to HEY\n3) on HackerOne\n4) developed by people at Basecamp\n5) of $5000\n6) stored XSS\n7) affecting email messages\n8) triage, bounty, fix, severity upgraded to critical, all in less than 24 h from reporting\n9) anything about impact?\n10) or technical details?\n\nI couldn't fit all of that in a tweet and didn't plan to do so. I have  only \u003c 2000 followers, but I think most are aspiring bug hunters and some may ask about it (in fact someone's already asking, apparently another participant to your program). So I'd just like to be sure not to cause a problem.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2020-09-16T15:59:40.304Z","updated_at":"2020-09-16T15:59:40.304Z","actor":{"username":"jouko","cleared":false,"url":"/jouko","profile_picture_urls":{"me